==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ulna
<hw>Ul"na</hw> <pr>(⟦ucr⟧l"n⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.,
the elbow. See <er>Ell</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>The postaxial bone of the forearm, or brachium, corresponding to
the fibula of the hind limb. See <er>Radius</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(O. Eng. Law)</fld> <def>An ell; also, a yard.</def>
<rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ulnage</ent>⟦br⟧
